Some 2,000 illegally trafficked elephant tusks and hundreds of finished ivory products, including chess boards and sculptures, were set alight yesterday.

U.S. Ambassador to the United Nations Samantha Power who was at the burn said, "All of our countries can and must do more," Power said. The burning sends a clear message, she added, that "the only place ivory belongs and the only value ivory has is on elephants."

